Retrieved from Support Ticket:
{quote}
I am doing a full reindex of Confluence following an upgrade of the instance.
It seems that the indexing process is not optimised for full reindexing and therefore full reindexing can be very very slow and inefficient. So far reindexing has been going for 3 days and is about 60% of the way through!

*Although you can specify a "batch size" for indexing, still each item that is indexed seems to require its own queries to the database.* This results on a much higher load on the database server than is required.

For example, instead of doing a single query per item that requires indexing, you could fetch batches of data from the database in a single query for 100 items that need to be indexed, reducing the load on the database by 100 and significantly increasing the speed of indexing.

This really needs to be worked on to boost the time taken for large reindexing tasks (full reindex or where large sets of restricted pages have had permissions modified).
{quote}

